WEBVTT

00:06.498 --> 00:10.622
We lifted up with all of the angels and all of the saints who are already in the heavenlies.

00:10.682 --> 00:16.968
And we pray, Lord, that our praises would just echo along with all of them to your holiness, Lord.

00:17.449 --> 00:18.790
We are so grateful.

00:18.910 --> 00:26.237
We are humbled that we can stand before you, Lord, that you come, that you meet us in this place and all of your holiness.

00:26.297 --> 00:28.319
You bring your presence to us, Lord.

00:28.339 --> 00:35.026
And I pray that as we've engaged in worship tonight, Lord, as we look at some nuggets of truth from your word,

00:35.138 --> 00:39.563
that you would make yourself real to us, that you would make your presence known.

00:39.943 --> 00:47.712
God, that we would embrace walking into those spaces and those opportunities where we can just experience you as real and powerful and true.

00:48.213 --> 01:01.067
And God, we just pray that as we continue to just lean in and present tonight that you would be honored, that you would be glorified, that our hearts and our souls and our whole being Lord would just be drawn closer and closer to you.

01:01.548 --> 01:03.730
And we thank you, Lord, that you are God.

01:04.226 --> 01:07.812
wants to be near to us and continues to draw us to yourself.

01:08.433 --> 01:10.917
We just give you all the thanks and all of the praise.

01:11.197 --> 01:12.179
We love you, Lord.

01:12.439 --> 01:13.902
In Jesus' name, I pray.

01:14.743 --> 01:14.843
Amen.

01:14.863 --> 01:16.987
Amen.

01:17.007 --> 01:17.928
You can be seated.

01:20.953 --> 01:21.855
Oh, it's good.

01:21.955 --> 01:22.736
Isn't it good?

01:22.816 --> 01:25.421
My goodness.

01:26.142 --> 01:27.424
I could have our musicians come.

01:27.464 --> 01:31.250
Don't you think that would be a great way to just start every morning?

01:31.522 --> 01:36.370
Wouldn't we just, like, set our day in a whole new direction if we would just start out our morning?

01:36.410 --> 01:39.795
You know, the bad news, my friends, actually, is you can.

01:40.256 --> 01:41.558
Just crank up the tunes.

01:41.618 --> 01:44.242
We don't need all of that.

01:44.263 --> 01:45.885
We've got great tunes on the radio, too.

01:45.945 --> 01:49.731
But carving out that time sometimes is just a different kind of thing, isn't it?

01:50.052 --> 01:51.915
But it puts our hearts in such a great place.

01:53.477 --> 01:55.300
Well, I can't thank you enough for coming.

01:55.340 --> 01:58.866
We're five weeks into this season of Lent.

01:59.298 --> 02:01.081
You know, I love as I hear different people.

02:01.121 --> 02:06.569
I've been trying to read a bit more about Lent and hear what other people are preaching and things of that nature.

02:06.609 --> 02:16.163
And it's so funny to me because there tends to be this genuine or overwhelming tone, I should say, of like Lent, the most awful season of the year.

02:16.183 --> 02:26.738
So I really, as I was kind of navigating into this word tonight, I just thought it's worth asking the question, how's it going?

02:28.162 --> 02:30.125
Are you at that point in your journey?

02:30.185 --> 02:36.755
Have you started to discover some things in yourself that are maybe just a little bit painful?

02:36.795 --> 02:43.805
Have you been inviting the Lord into those places that you've been discovering?

02:43.825 --> 02:49.554
Or you may be in that space where you're still just kind of waiting.

02:50.178 --> 02:52.301
to see what he has for you in this season.

02:52.341 --> 03:03.719
You've maybe been navigating through it, you've given something up, you've been coming to church on Wednesdays, but you just haven't quite figured out what it is that God has for you in this journey.

03:03.779 --> 03:09.147
Whether you're in any one of those places, I want you to know that you're in a good place.

03:09.888 --> 03:11.250
And my hope tonight is I

03:11.554 --> 03:12.617
spend just a few minutes.

03:12.637 --> 03:15.704
It's just going to be a really quick message for all of you tonight.

03:15.745 --> 03:16.426
And I do mean that.

03:16.446 --> 03:19.354
I know I usually get a little bit lengthy, but it really will be quick tonight.

03:19.835 --> 03:28.978
But my hope is just to encourage each of us to stay committed to the journey, not because we're obligated to.

03:29.538 --> 03:39.409
I hope you've heard us as we've been kind of navigating into this season of Lent, that we're really under no obligation to be a part of this experience or the practices of Lent.

03:39.429 --> 03:45.155
God doesn't love us more or less if we do or we don't choose to participate in this.

03:45.596 --> 03:52.564
But it was in a conversation earlier today that gave me just a little bit more perspective on how it is that Lent came to be.

03:53.064 --> 03:58.130
So I want to take a few minutes and just share that with you, give you a little bit bigger picture of

03:58.338 --> 04:06.049
Why it is that the church for thousands of years actually has embraced this tradition of Lent.

04:06.830 --> 04:10.755
And interestingly enough, it all actually traces back to baptism.

04:11.817 --> 04:13.038
It's kind of interesting, isn't it?

04:13.078 --> 04:22.932
If you've taken our baptism class, you'll know that when we look at the scriptures, the scriptures are just quite clear that once a person comes to faith, they should get baptized.

04:22.992 --> 04:27.378
And we see over and over again in the scriptures that this would happen fairly quickly.

04:27.458 --> 04:30.525
So people would come to faith, they'd say, oh, well, I should just be baptized now.

04:30.565 --> 04:37.221
So they always kind of came, you know, belief first, putting their faith in Christ, but then fairly soon after that they would get baptized.

04:37.703 --> 04:44.178
Now, somewhere along the line, I don't know exactly when, and I don't know exactly why, but a couple of hundred years,

04:44.258 --> 04:51.771
after Jesus had risen into heaven after he had ascended, the church actually started to change their practice a little bit of baptism.

04:51.831 --> 04:53.454
And this is what's kind of interesting.

04:53.995 --> 04:57.300
And again, I don't know why, but I could speculate a little bit.

04:57.921 --> 05:05.234
Because I tend to wonder if maybe they started to discover that there was a bit of this clinging to that act of baptism and they were maybe

05:05.282 --> 05:11.178
discovering that some of those new believers weren't really growing past that stage of a new believer.

05:11.839 --> 05:17.113
They kind of figured out getting themselves right with God for eternity, but then it maybe rested there.

05:17.514 --> 05:21.906
So where the church actually moved to is before they would baptize

05:21.986 --> 05:25.510
new believers, they would put them through this process of a catechism.

05:26.071 --> 05:33.199
It's kind of like, if you grew up in those traditions that do confirmation for teenagers, it's kind of like that concept.

05:34.000 --> 05:35.962
And it, of course, changed over the years.

05:36.022 --> 05:46.514
But at one point, they actually required somebody to go through a two-year process of being catechized before they would actually put them through water baptism.

05:46.818 --> 05:49.763
And water baptism would always happen on Easter Sunday.

05:50.183 --> 05:52.567
So it tended to correspond with kind of this time of year.

05:52.627 --> 06:11.236
Now what was different about the historical practice was that they of course did some of the things that you would imagine and are similar to the traditions that kind of still hold true in some churches today where they would of course spend time teaching and instructing and giving them some knowledge and understanding about the things of faith.

06:11.256 --> 06:15.282
I would imagine they were required to memorize and things of that nature.

06:15.394 --> 06:24.530
which isn't unlike what happens today, but they also spent a good amount of the time then encouraging them in some of these spiritual practices.

06:24.610 --> 06:32.843
So things like fasting, meditating on scripture, self-reflection, solitude, some of those kinds of things.

06:33.303 --> 06:49.949
And what they started to discover is as these people would come through this journey and get to the point of their baptism at Easter Sunday, they discovered that that process became so meaningful and enriching for them in terms of their faith and their journey with the Lord.

06:49.989 --> 06:53.394
And so what the church finally came to realize is, well,

06:53.826 --> 06:57.772
If this is so good for them, wouldn't it be good for all of us?

06:58.833 --> 07:05.603
And because it all happened just before Easter, it kind of became the beginning of what is now understood as Lent.

07:06.083 --> 07:19.282
It was just that challenge to the church community as a whole to take a little bit of extra time to press into some of these things with the goal of making a little bit more room for an experience with the Lord.

07:19.810 --> 07:27.867
So you see, this season of Lent was never actually about fasting, giving something up.

07:28.529 --> 07:33.198
It was never actually about self-reflection or any of those other things.

07:33.279 --> 07:36.786
They just happened to be the tried and true methods

07:36.962 --> 07:46.214
of the ultimate goal, which was, of course, to experience more of God a deeper, more fulfilling experience of this faith journey with Him.

07:46.935 --> 07:51.080
So we have to be careful because it wasn't about putting more icons of God in their life.

07:51.140 --> 07:52.702
And let me explain what I mean by that.

07:53.103 --> 07:55.686
It wasn't about attaching themselves to religiosity.

07:56.747 --> 07:58.489
Jesus actually had some pretty strong words.

07:58.550 --> 08:02.034
So what I mean by this word of religiosity is

08:02.178 --> 08:09.425
being so tied to religious things or actions or it can be activities, any of those kinds of things.

08:09.886 --> 08:12.909
And Jesus really actually had some very strong things that he wanted to say to this.

08:13.009 --> 08:15.771
Actually, I'm gonna put this one up on the screen, Matthew 23, 27.

08:16.973 --> 08:21.937
Jesus said this, he said, whoa to you, teachers of the law and Pharisees, you hypocrites.

08:22.898 --> 08:30.706
You're like whitewashed tombs, which look beautiful on the outside, but on the inside are full of the bones of the dead and everything unclean.

08:31.874 --> 08:34.519
Now the Pharisees were the most religious people of the day.

08:34.559 --> 08:36.604
They kept all of the laws.

08:36.644 --> 08:40.251
They observed all those things that were expected of them.

08:40.291 --> 08:43.458
But Jesus, when he looked at them, he said, you know what?

08:43.498 --> 08:47.827
Those things are not giving you a living encounter of the living God.

08:47.887 --> 08:51.474
They're producing something that is dead and unclean in you.

08:52.066 --> 09:01.051
So please understand that when we talk about some of these practices, this journey of Lent, it's not at all about putting religiosity into our lives.

09:01.532 --> 09:08.050
It is about getting ourselves to a point of having these deeper, more meaningful encounters with the Lord.

09:08.642 --> 09:17.212
Now, a lot of us in the room had some experience with Lent, maybe as kids, maybe in traditions where we didn't necessarily understand it.

09:18.214 --> 09:20.957
So it was kind of that, and I certainly had this in my life.

09:20.977 --> 09:23.941
It was kind of that thing where you just gave something up because that's what you were supposed to do.

09:23.961 --> 09:30.809
And so we didn't actually pursue the value that God had in the journey for us.

09:31.329 --> 09:38.418
And quite honestly, when that's the approach that we take to those things, it becomes quite empty and meaningless.

09:38.882 --> 09:42.866
It's no different than what Jesus was saying to those Pharisees about looking whitewashed.

09:42.886 --> 09:44.808
You can look good on the outside, right?

09:45.489 --> 09:49.293
But on the inside, it just creates dead bones and things that are unclean.

09:50.594 --> 10:06.450
So what I came to realize is that when we were pursuing this, when we kind of have that heart and that mind about needing to do these things, we kind of get into this place of assuming that we need to attain some kind of perfection for lack of a better word.

10:06.914 --> 10:11.960
We try to somehow achieve the approval of God by doing these things.

10:12.040 --> 10:22.132
And if we do them well enough, that has to be the ultimate goal when we think that our faith and our relationship to Him is somehow based on our achievement or what it is that we do.

10:22.172 --> 10:26.677
But you see, God doesn't call us to perfection.

10:26.738 --> 10:30.522
One day when we make it to heaven, we will be perfect.

10:31.163 --> 10:33.906
And we can look forward to that day, right?

10:34.466 --> 10:40.094
But you see, when we're here on this side of heaven, the thing that he calls us to is pursuit.

10:41.537 --> 10:42.959
So let me put those things together.

10:42.999 --> 10:46.424
God does not call us to perfection.

10:46.484 --> 10:49.288
He calls us to pursuit.

10:50.490 --> 10:53.915
So the verse that I want to focus on tonight comes out of the book of Jeremiah.

10:54.156 --> 10:56.079
It's a very familiar one, Jeremiah 29, 13.

10:56.219 --> 11:03.730
It says this, you will seek me and find me when you seek me with all your heart.

11:04.322 --> 11:12.198
If you've ever received an email from me, you know that this is like my signature line on my emails, because it's one of those things that I need to just keep before my own eyes.

11:12.218 --> 11:17.469
And you know, the interesting thing, if we read that verse, you will seek me and find me when you seek me with all your heart.

11:17.489 --> 11:19.133
It's a pretty easy one to understand.

11:19.173 --> 11:20.576
The language is simple enough.

11:21.558 --> 11:25.426
But I want you to know that I took a little bit of time to look into this word, seek.

11:25.922 --> 11:28.608
Because here's the downfall of the English language.

11:29.049 --> 11:32.937
The English language we use so many words to mean so many different things.

11:33.499 --> 11:40.113
And so when we use a word like seek, I would imagine for most of us, like what we, the picture that comes to mind is looking for.

11:40.173 --> 11:45.906
You know, when we're seeking for something, when we're looking for it, you know, that

11:46.178 --> 11:48.241
If we'll do that, then we'll find God.

11:48.261 --> 11:51.646
If we look for Him, we'll find Him if we look for Him with all of our hearts.

11:52.107 --> 12:02.522
But I want you to know that the Hebrew language, and this first comes out of the Old Testament, so it was written in Hebrew, the Hebrew language is so beautiful and so full and so much more descriptive.

12:03.002 --> 12:08.210
In so many of their words, they have different words for what we would have in

12:08.354 --> 12:09.395
for a common language.

12:09.836 --> 12:15.284
And so I looked at this word seek, and it certainly means what we would think this looking for kind of thing.

12:15.304 --> 12:19.670
But I wanna share with you some of the other words that are really attached to the Hebrew word.

12:19.710 --> 12:20.651
I think it's batak.

12:20.871 --> 12:21.833
I don't know if I'm saying that right.

12:22.534 --> 12:37.394
But some of the other definitions that are tied to this word, and there are these, ask, care for, diligently inquire, question, make, inquisition,

12:38.882 --> 12:42.009
So you see this process of seeking the Lord?

12:42.049 --> 12:49.624
It's really meant to be one of almost curiosity in asking, there's this real element of inquiring.

12:49.685 --> 12:58.002
I love that phrase, diligently inquire, that we're supposed to kind of engage in if we truly do want to find the Lord.

12:58.082 --> 13:11.738
So I want to just encourage you, as you navigate through the rest of this Lenten journey, if it's something that you've given up, if it's something that you're doing, whatever the case may be, I want to encourage you along the way, make sure you're asking some questions.

13:13.240 --> 13:20.769
Because if our goal is to seek God in this, then we need to be asking questions of Him.

13:21.150 --> 13:23.473
We need to be diligently inquiring.

13:23.513 --> 13:28.018
So it might be things like, Lord, why did I act that way?

13:29.378 --> 13:30.599
Why did I do that thing?

13:30.660 --> 13:34.064
Why does it exactly you want me to learn from this?

13:35.806 --> 13:42.013
Whether right now you feel like you're like getting that something from land or maybe you're in that place of like, I don't know, I'm still waiting.

13:42.634 --> 13:44.476
Well, that might be a worthwhile question to ask.

13:44.856 --> 13:49.722
Lord, what is it that you want me to be getting from this season?

13:49.782 --> 13:56.370
Lord, what is it that you want me to understand because it seems so quiet right now?

13:58.210 --> 14:00.933
You might wanna ask them, too, Lord, how is it you're moving?

14:00.973 --> 14:02.895
Help me to see these things.

14:04.276 --> 14:06.499
And now what I love about this verse, I'm gonna bring it back.

14:06.519 --> 14:09.362
And I remember it says, we should seek him and find him.

14:10.423 --> 14:15.108
You will seek me and find me when you seek me with all your heart.

14:16.809 --> 14:20.313
And I believe that becomes actually the beauty of this verse.

14:21.234 --> 14:25.138
It's not just the seeking, it's the heart with which we do it.

14:25.666 --> 14:36.002
Because you see, when we seek from a place that is our heart with all of our heart, then we start to seek him from a sense of desire to know him rather than from a sense of duty.

14:36.022 --> 14:42.973
And I dare say that sometimes when we navigate into these seasons of Lent, it can start to feel like our duty.

14:42.993 --> 14:51.026
If we haven't figured out that really the heart of this is to have a desire to have more of him in this.

14:51.362 --> 14:59.173
And we have to be very cautious about that because when we pursue God from a sense of duty, it leads to that perfectionist thinking.

15:00.215 --> 15:07.065
Because either we did something or we didn't do something, we've accomplished it or not, we did it all the way or we didn't quite make it.

15:07.105 --> 15:11.872
And when we haven't quite made it, then we get into that space of thinking that we've somehow failed.

15:12.212 --> 15:18.802
And you see, when we do it from duty, and then we don't sense that we've moved any closer to the Lord,

15:20.098 --> 15:26.428
It creates a bit of a conflict for us because then we're faced with a couple of propositions.

15:27.590 --> 15:30.955
One might be that this faith thing just really doesn't work.

15:33.299 --> 15:39.548
Or maybe, and this happens for some, they start to think, I don't think God works.

15:41.672 --> 15:48.242
At best, we might be asking the question, I think maybe me doing this doesn't work.

15:48.930 --> 15:50.452
And I would say that's the best scenario.

15:51.233 --> 15:55.999
Because if that's the question that you're asking, then I would suggest that you're absolutely right.

15:57.441 --> 16:00.445
Because we are not called to perfect prayer.

16:00.505 --> 16:03.409
We're not called to perfect fasting.

16:03.449 --> 16:06.032
We're not called to perfect Bible reading.

16:06.333 --> 16:10.578
We are called to pursue a perfect God.

16:11.586 --> 16:19.659
and prayer and fasting and meditation and all of these things are really beautiful instruments to help us in the pursuit.

16:21.042 --> 16:23.185
But they themselves cannot be the focus.

16:24.988 --> 16:38.290
Otherwise, we will always be tempted and lured into that place of duty and perfection instead of keeping ourselves in a place of pursuit and

16:39.874 --> 16:41.476
I forgot my other word, pursuit and desire.

16:41.536 --> 16:42.917
That was what I was looking for.

16:42.977 --> 16:46.581
So anyway, we are called to pursue this perfect God.

16:46.641 --> 16:55.329
I do want to take just a moment because, you know, if you've been navigating in this Lenten season with us, you know that we tend to put emphasis on this idea of fasting.

16:55.790 --> 16:56.991
And I've talked with lots of people.

16:57.031 --> 17:01.635
I know a lot of you have chosen to engage in that and whatever it looks at, whatever that looks like for you.

17:01.655 --> 17:03.037
It can look in lots of different ways.

17:03.457 --> 17:08.402
But I do want to encourage you to realize that there are lots of other practices

17:08.930 --> 17:15.841
that we can do to kind of just shake ourselves up a little bit and create a little bit more room for an experience with the Lord.

17:15.881 --> 17:23.372
Many of you have probably read books or articles about things called spiritual disciplines or spiritual practices.

17:23.432 --> 17:34.770
There's things like solitude and memorization and all kinds of these other things that we can certainly do as part of this expression.

17:34.978 --> 17:55.764
For whatever it's worth, if any of those things are of interest to you, I'll probably just link some things in our next celebration insider if you receive the insider, because it's valuable sometimes to just kind of look and explore some of those other things that are out there, especially if you find that the method that you're engaging in isn't necessarily bringing you to the place that you want to be.

17:55.844 --> 17:58.046
So let me ask you this question.

17:58.146 --> 18:01.871
I started this message with the same question that I'm gonna ask, end it with.

18:03.313 --> 18:04.274
How's it going?

18:05.154 --> 18:06.335
How's your Lenten journey?

18:06.396 --> 18:11.041
Because maybe you needed just a little heart adjustment tonight.

18:11.442 --> 18:22.655
It's my hope that there are some of you in this room who just needed to kind of have that realization that you need to shift your heart a bit away from this idea of perfection and more towards pursuit.

18:23.977 --> 18:25.399
It is easier said than done.

18:25.439 --> 18:31.506
But if that's you, let me encourage you, begin asking some questions.

18:32.226 --> 18:37.395
Okay, now if this isn't something you've done before, I will caution you, it feels weird at first.

18:38.998 --> 18:40.000
I'm just being honest.

18:40.360 --> 18:45.469
Like that space of like just well lord, you know, and for some people it's very natural, very easy.

18:45.529 --> 18:50.198
Some of us have been doing it for a while, but if it's not something that you've done before, it feels a little weird at first.

18:50.558 --> 18:57.330
To just ask him the question, but remember, seeking him means diligently inquiring.

18:57.986 --> 19:08.016
My very first, when I started Lent this year, I will tell you, I usually do a lot of things for Lent, and I don't say that to make myself sound holy.

19:08.036 --> 19:12.240
I say that because it's just, I need to challenge myself.

19:12.340 --> 19:13.742
I get real complacent.

19:13.762 --> 19:16.504
I can get real complacent and comfortable with my place of spirituality.

19:16.544 --> 19:22.250
So I usually do many things during this season, but this year as I navigated into it, I was just struggling.

19:22.270 --> 19:26.354
I couldn't figure out what it should be, like what it would look like,

19:26.498 --> 19:42.418
You know, I didn't want to just go back to some of the old standby because I just wanted to have purpose and meaning and So I spent a good amount of time before the Lord just asking them and so I didn't start on Ash Wednesday because I didn't have it yet It took me a few days of continuing to ask the question Lord like

19:43.010 --> 19:43.712
What should it be?

19:43.752 --> 19:47.099
Where am I not meeting you well?

19:47.159 --> 19:48.502
What does that look like?

19:48.562 --> 19:57.000
I won't get into the whole story because it doesn't really matter right now, but I will tell you that the thing that I gave up, some of you have heard the story, is I had to give up sitting on the comfortable furniture in my house.

19:58.383 --> 19:59.666
What a weird thing, right?

19:59.970 --> 20:06.877
So no sofa sitting for me, no comfy chair sitting, unless we had company, I had that caveat with the Lord, like then it was acceptable, but otherwise I couldn't.

20:07.517 --> 20:11.541
But there's just some of those things and I discovered in that process that the Lord really met me there.

20:11.581 --> 20:20.750
There was something for me in that process because I had already kind of been asking him the questions about what it was that I needed to get out of this particular season.

20:21.271 --> 20:28.818
So let me encourage you, if you don't know what to ask, why don't you just ask some other people what they think would be good questions to ask?

20:29.154 --> 20:31.236
Ask somebody that you're sitting with during soup tonight.

20:32.257 --> 20:33.839
They just might have some great insight for you.

20:33.859 --> 20:40.546
But there are also some here tonight who have desired to know the Lord more for quite some time.

20:40.607 --> 20:47.434
But there seems to somehow be this gap between where you are and where it is that you want to be.

20:47.514 --> 20:50.257
Quite honestly, that's always my hope.

20:50.758 --> 20:58.386
I hope that gap will exist because I know that I will never arrive with the Lord, never have full understanding of Him until maybe when we get to heaven one day.

20:58.818 --> 21:03.506
But I want to caution you that wanting it, desiring it, is not enough.

21:04.908 --> 21:11.218
If you want to close that gap between where you are and where you want to be, it requires a commitment.

21:13.402 --> 21:18.630
Vince Lombardi, I grabbed a Vince Lombardi quote for you tonight, had said this once and it's so good and powerful.

21:18.671 --> 21:25.682
He said, most people fail not because of a lack of desire, but because of a lack of commitment.

21:27.138 --> 21:29.781
So I want you to know I'm not perfect in my pursuit of the Lord.

21:29.801 --> 21:31.123
I've discovered I don't need to be.

21:32.344 --> 21:35.288
The more I grow, the more I discover I have more growth I need to do.

21:35.408 --> 21:40.314
And the more there is to discover about who he is and what this faith journey looks like.

21:41.275 --> 21:44.599
But I am committed to pursuing him.

21:44.639 --> 21:50.226
And it's my challenge to you tonight that you might take steps to make that commitment as well.

21:51.407 --> 21:52.188
But here's the thing.

21:52.248 --> 21:56.914
Commitment is not a one time done deal.

21:57.698 --> 22:01.363
We need to make our commitments, but then we need to manage them.

22:01.383 --> 22:13.660
And managing sometimes means recommitting daily or weekly or hourly, whatever the case may be, but they usually require us to do a little bit of massaging and managing of those things.

22:14.661 --> 22:27.378
So you might need to recommit yourself to that goal of pursuing him, and maybe you need to give up on your commitment to the method that you've been using, and maybe look for a different method.

22:27.938 --> 22:30.381
Start exploring some of these other spiritual disciplines.

22:30.401 --> 22:34.226
Start experiencing some of these practices that the church has been doing for years.

22:34.727 --> 22:42.136
And maybe for you tonight, when you're sitting at the table, it might be worth asking the question, hey, have any of you done some things like just that are different, that are out of the ordinary?

22:42.156 --> 22:53.290
Because I'll tell you, if we'll just be willing to explore those things that are out of the ordinary, you will, I'm telling you, have an encounter with the God who is truly extraordinary.

22:53.330 --> 22:56.434
And that's what this season of Lent is all about.

22:57.026 --> 23:01.971
So let me pray for you and then we're gonna break and we're gonna go spend some time fellowshiping, grab a bowl of soup.

23:02.291 --> 23:07.917
And I hope that you'll take some opportunity to just talk with each other about whatever it is that the Lord has been putting on your heart tonight.

23:08.558 --> 23:13.943
And then maybe in the quietness of your time when you get home, ask him a few questions as well and see what he's got for you in that.

23:14.604 --> 23:15.024
Let's pray.

23:17.046 --> 23:24.914
Oh, Lord, it is truly such a privilege that you do desire a relationship with us.

23:25.122 --> 23:30.529
and got him so grateful that you can be found by us, not understood completely, Lord.

23:30.569 --> 23:36.155
We know that you are just so much greater than anything that we can imagine, but we know that you can be found.

23:36.716 --> 23:51.314
And we just pray, Lord, that we will be a people who continue to commit ourselves to the pursuit of having more and more and grander and richer and deeper experiences with you, Lord, because we know that is what you pursue with us as well.

23:51.746 --> 23:53.209
We thank you so much for this time.

23:53.229 --> 23:58.378
We pray that you would just be honored and glorified at the tables tonight and in our conversations.

23:59.079 --> 24:02.124
And Lord, as we go tonight, keep us safe as well out on the roads.

24:02.324 --> 24:03.086
We love you so much.

24:03.146 --> 24:04.168
In Jesus' name, I pray.

24:04.188 --> 24:06.371
Amen.

24:06.392 --> 24:08.595
If you've got young ones, you can pick them up this evening.

24:08.635 --> 24:11.340
But again, as always, we ask you to kind of let our students finish up.

24:11.380 --> 24:14.245
They're going to go until eight o'clock tonight, but then go grab yourself some soup.

24:14.305 --> 24:16.189
And I hope you enjoy some time with each other as well.

24:16.229 --> 24:17.010
Thanks for coming out.

